commit.message:
Add type hints

And perform several other minor changes:
- Fix typos in comments and docstrings.
- Reformat 'if' oneliners into blocks with newlines.
- Change the indentation on several places.
- Add FIXMEs to places which were found to be problematic.

Part of the type hints was guessed via the tool 'monkeytype', then they
were manually checked and updated.
Add '.idea' directory to .gitignore
Stop explicitly passing arguments to super() function calls

Drop Python 2 code

Remove conditional imports that try to import Python 2 or Python 3 bits,
depending on the version.

Drop dependency on six

Six is a Python 2--Python 3 compatibility library. It does not need to
be included in Python 3 only codebase.

Stop explicit inheritance from object

Since Python 3, only new-style classes are used, and Foo(object): is no
longer necessary.

Remove Travis CI link from README

We are not using Travis anymore.
